    Title: Philebus
    Locus: 16 C
By: Plato
Tags:
  - Discernment-Truth=Reality=The One and the Many
  - Creation=The World Begins in Perfection
---
The ancients, who were our betters and nearer the gods than we are, handed down
the tradition, that whatever things are said to be are composed of one and
many.
